c. With the initial list [1, 2, 3, 4, 5], how would you append an element, remove an element,
and extend it with another list [7, 8, 9]?

a_list = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]
for i in range(7, 8, 9):
    a_list.append(i)

fruits = ['apple', 'banana', 'cherry']

fruits.remove("banana")

